                        MEMORY LAYOUT
====================================================================
A typical C program memory layout:

+------------------------+
|        TEXT            |  (Compiled machine code)
+------------------------+
|   GLOBAL / STATIC      |  (Initialized global variables)
+------------------------+
|   BSS SEGMENT          |  (Uninitialized globals)
+------------------------+
|        HEAP            |  (Dynamic memory - grows upward)
|                        |
|                        |
+------------------------+
|                        |
|                        |
|        STACK           |  (Function calls - grows downward)
+------------------------+
STACK:
- Stores local variables
- Stores function parameters
- Stores return addresses
- Automatically managed

HEAP:
- Used for dynamic memory
- Manually managed (malloc/free)
- Slower but flexible
