====================================================================
                COMMON POINTER MISTAKES
====================================================================
1) Using uninitialized pointer
    int *p; *p = 5;   // CRASH
2) Memory leak
    malloc() without free()
3) Double free
    free(p);
    free(p);  // UNDEFINED BEHAVIOR
4) Dangling pointer
    free(p);
    *p = 10;  // INVALID (memory freed)
Best Practice:
    After free(p);
    p = NULL;
